OL,5, A whistle-blower in the case of an     
OL,6, autistic man who has been detained in  
OL,7, hospital since 2001 says he feels      
OL,8, complicit in his "neglect and abuse".  
OL,10,FA BBC investigation found 100 people   
OL,11,Fwith learning disabilities have been   
OL,12,Fheld in specialist hospitals for 20    
OL,13,Fyears or more, including Tony Hickmott.
OL,15,FHis parents are fighting to get him    
OL,16,Frehoused in the community.             
OL,18,FA support worker at a hospital where Mr
OL,19,FHickmott has been detained said he was 
OL,20,Fthe "loneliest man in the hospital".   
